import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="height", y=data.index, data=data, color='b')
    ax.axvline(x=data['height'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Height: {:.2f}'.format(data['height'].mean()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the average height of individuals in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    name_count = data.groupby('name').count().reset_index()
    name_count = name_count.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="name", y="count", data=name_count)
    ax.axhline(y=name_count['count'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(name_count['count'].max()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean Age: {data["age"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution for individuals with a certain name?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
